I can not believe that a 5 or 6 year old child has a more detailed memory of the nightmare than I do. She surprised me with a photo of Tom yesterday. I was speechless well, breathless!I was mortified and upset. Not at Tom, but my sisiter because I have done such a good job of burying these memories far far beneath the surface that it shocked me. I had flashbacks. It drained me. Why am I upset with my sister? This is not her trying to hurt me. I calm down and call her. It will be the first time we have spoken in months. We have dissagreements then come back to eachother. My love for her overshadows the words I do not speak, and she knows that and I know that it is reciprocated.I do love her so and I protected her as long as I could, but I had to make a run for it. 

I am thinking of only one memory of Martha and it is at the townhouses in Bensenville. The ghetto. Where Tom and mom would fight insatibly and I would find my mom at the top of the stairs with a huge knife in her hand, crying. I would comfort her, but i could not understand why it happened over and over. I remember when Tom got pissed and threw a beer bottle or a bowl at our television and it just sat,forever, broken in our livingroom. Just like our family. Broken & Wounded.

I do not have the compassion for my mom that my sister does. She does not remember mom having her bar buddies sneak into our room (Sister sleeping right next to me in anothet twin bed)and try to fuck me, and I would have to beat them off or scream or something. Mom said the only way she could sleep with this one particular fellow was if his friend had someone to fuck. So mom brought him  home for me! A 13 year old? That is fucked up! She was a few years younger than I am now. I drink and get trashed. I would never do that to my child. My sister says that I dont undertand because I dont have any kids. But let me tell you, I can guarantee that no matter how fucked up baby sis gets, she would never do that to her kid. So I do understand. Choices. For every action there is a reaction. S did not , thank God, have to pull mom out of bars to come home Monday so us kids could go to school. If we couldnt find her in DuPage county I stayed home and waited for her to stroll in at her leasure because she could of card less. We were a liability. We held her down, so she gave up on us.(and herself). Mom had a gun blown off in the house many times. Men exposing their dicks on the diningroom table was normal. I remember Tom having a hysterical fun time throwing darts at our dog, mom, and S. When I saw that I said ENOUGH! I called her dad  and told him things were really bad and he better come and get his kids. It was very hard to 'betray' my mom like that, but I cared about the welfare of sister & brother. God knows what older brother E had to endure before I could get him and have mom relinquish all rights as his guardian and parent, and I was now his guardian beacuse I was 18 now. I took E back to the Seattle area with me and it was no picnic there eaither, but that can be for later.
The funny thing is that when I tried to commit suicide the last time in the late 80's, I was forced into therapy. Thank God, it saved the small sense of sanity I had left.During one session I told him I could never understand  why I  had such alcholholic ahole's for boyfriends and they would hit me and leave me for dead in a ditch. The therapist told me it was not my 'fault' and that it was all I knew from growing up in the household/environment that I did. Whew..was I glad to know I was okay, and not deserving of these constant beatings. I think I would rather get pillaged like that, then to deal with the emotional scarring of verbal abuse. Those scars don't heal.
Well I am done for now. Sis I hate to feel these feelings, but I figure we can do it together. We are all we ever had anyway. Just 4 lost siblings hiding in the back of the upstairs closet with weapons, hiding from the monster.

Nex,t I got asked by the entertainment specialist to sing at the largest fair in our state, The Evergreen State Fair here in lil ole' Monroe. I will be singing the National Anthem before about 5,000 people in the grandstands, to the thousands at the fair(within ear shot).
I will be singing August 30th before Blue Oyster Cult. Go Go Godzilla! The fair could hit over a million attendees this year. Bad for traffic. Good for the economy.
Anyway, my bosses wife had surgery and I am going to visit her tonight. I made a personalized coloring book of her friends, and her husband(my boss). I feel it's never too old to color. If you are too old,then you know you have surpassed the threshold of insanity. 
Gotta fly. Take care. Remember, life is not about the amount of breaths you take, but about the moments that take your breath away. Peace out.
